#### Here we decide on the thresholds we want to test the FDRs for

```{.python .input  n=7}
thresholds = np.logspace(-1,2, num=100)/1000
thresholds
```

<div class='outputs' n=7>

</div>

#### Here we calculate the FDRs at the different thresholds

```{.python .input  n=96}
%%time
fdrs_d = {}
tt_fdrs_d={}
for threshold in thresholds:
    M = db.query("SELECT count(p_value) FROM motif_average_scores where p_value < '" + str(threshold) + "'").getresult()[0][0]
    tt_M = db.query("SELECT count(p_value) FROM motif_average_scores where tt_p_value < '" + str(threshold) + "'").getresult()[0][0]
    N = db.query("SELECT count(shuffled_p_value)FROM motif_average_scores where shuffled_p_value < '" + str(threshold) + "'").getresult()[0][0]
    tt_N = db.query("SELECT count(shuffled_p_value)FROM motif_average_scores where tt_shuffled_p_value < '" + str(threshold) + "'").getresult()[0][0]  
#     print(threshold, N, M)
#     print(threshold, tt_N, tt_M)
    fdrs_d[threshold] = (N+1)/(M+1) #adding 1 on all sides to not have devide by zero error
    tt_fdrs_d[threshold] = (tt_N+1)/(tt_M+1)

```
